<button class="servicesTab"> Library </button>

<div class="panel">
    <hr />
    <p style="margin-left:1%; margin-right:1%">
        The library is a one of the most welcoming spaces for the students at university where they can meet,
        learn, and study. The University of Newcastle provides some of the best libraries on its campuses.
        Callaghan campus has different libraries. Auchmuty library and Huxley library at Callaghan campus
        provides you with the best facility to borrow any book, book a room for a meeting or to group study
        in the learning lounge. Opening and closing hours of the library may differ for various reasons.
    </p>

    <iframe src="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1W2U4X81Qd4bMi-hsSWis-mmexIIwRNV6/preview" width="65%" height="400" allow="autoplay"></iframe>
    <br /> <br />

    <h3>Auchmuty Library:</h3>
    <p style="margin-left:1%; margin-right:1%">
        On the western side of Callaghan campus, Auchmuty library is located near the Shortland
        building. The learning lounge is on level 3 where you can study in a group freely. On the ground
        floor there’s the AIC (Auchmuty Information Commons). There are also rooms available for
        booking as well if you want to do schedule a meeting or something else. Both spaces are open
        24/7 for students.
    </p>

    <h3>Learning Lounge:</h3>
    <p style="margin-left:1%; margin-right:1%">
        The learning lounge is on 3rd level, and you need to have a student card to access this space.
        The learning lounge is open 24/7. You can study on PCs, and you are also allowed to bring your own
        laptops with you for collaborative studies.  There is a student kitchen. Vending machine are
        there for refreshments. Microwaves are also placed there if you want to heat up your food.
    </p>

    <h3>Auchmuty Information Commons:</h3>
    <p style="margin-left:1%; margin-right:1%">
        The AIC is open 24/7. It is a space with PCs and rooms in it. Scanners, printers, and computers
        for students can be found in this area. You should have your student card if you want to print
        out anything you desire. Students can also borrow laptops and books from here in staff hours. A
        student card is required to do that as well. The AIC also has a café which is open till the afternoon.
    </p>

    <h3>Finding Books:</h3>
    <p style="margin-left:1%; margin-right:1%">
        Students can go onto the website to find journals, books, and articles by searching on the
        library search. That can be found here: <a href="https://www.newcastle.edu.au/library/access/search">Library Search</a>
        Click on this link and search for the book you want to read. Once you find the book, you can
        either go to library and ask the attendant to lend the book to you or you can also borrow online
        by clicking the e-book option. If the electronic version of that book is available, you can get it
        online. Otherwise, you will have to borrow it from the librarian. If you borrow a physical copy
        you are required to return the book back within a certain period. Otherwise, you will be
        charged with a fine every week until you make a return.
    </p>

    <h3>Document Printing:</h3>
    <p style="margin-left:1%; margin-right:1%">
        Open the document on your PC and print it by choosing the appropriate printer. You first need
        to put a balance into the printer to pay for your printing. After sending to print, go to the
        printer and swipe your student card on it and select “my print jobs” and then “release”.
    </p>
