<button class="servicesTab"> Personal Support and Counselling </button>

<div class="panel">
    <hr />
    <p style="margin-left:1%; margin-right:1%">
        As we all know, a person’s mental health is as important as anyone’s physical health. You
        should take care of your mental health to help you navigate through your life and to be
        successful. If you are an international student, you could face some difficulties which may cause
        some mental stress to you as you don’t have your family here or any old friends. The Uni is here
        to help, we will treat you as your family and we will give you special treatment if needed. Feel
        free to contact counselling and support services from the Uni.
    </p>

    <iframe src="https://drive.google.com/file/d/12IIc1mM-uR2RtoTJKKF_MFY2w4FVKGPX/preview" width="65%" height="400" allow="autoplay"></iframe>
    <br />

    <p style="margin-left:1%; margin-right:1%">
        The University of Newcastle provides a wide range of facilities for student support like
        consultation services and online counselling on skype. When you are in contact with a wellbeing
        advisor, the information you share will remain confidential between you and your consultant.
        We have a team of experienced psychologists who can help you work through your problems
    </p>

    <h3>How to Access:</h3>
    <p style="margin-left:1%; margin-right:1%">
        We have a team of experienced psychologists who can help you work through your problems
        and lead you towards the solutions in any way they can. To book an appointment, go to the link
        here: <a href="https://www.newcastle.edu.au/current-students/support/personal/counselling/access-support">Access Support</a>
        There you will see an option for an online form. Open the form and kindly complete it. If
        you need help regarding the registration form, please call 4921 6622 or email counselling@newcastle.edu.au.
        Students can also visit student services at level 2 between 9:00 am to 5:00 pm and you can
        book your appointment there. You can arrange the earliest date you need whenever possible.
    </p>

    <h3>Online Drop In:</h3>
    <p style="margin-left:1%; margin-right:1%">
        There are no appointments needed for online drop ins. During semester days online drop in is available
        at different times to help you over zoom or skype. You can get the timeslots from here:
        <a href="https://www.newcastle.edu.au/current-students/support/personal/counselling/online-drop-in">Online Drop In</a>.
    </p>
    <p style="margin-left:1%; margin-right:1%">
        If you want to attend these sessions:
        <ul>
            <li>Download the skype app.</li>
            <li>Add contact Uononlinecounsellor.</li>
            <li>Send a request to be added.</li>
        </ul>
    </p>

    <h3>What kind of help will the counsellor provide me?</h3>
    <p style="margin-left:1%; margin-right:1%">
        First, a counsellor in the online session or during face to face as well will ask for your student
        card and your details just to confirm the appointment. Then they will start the session and will
        ask questions from you like what kind of problems you are facing, and what are the things going
        on in your daily life? How is your diet? What about your sleep? After this discussion the advisor
        will guide you in different ways to help lead you towards a solution of living a better and
        healthier lifestyle.
    </p>

    <p>
        You should not be worried about the information you share because all of it will be kept private
        and confidential between you and your advisor.
    </p>

    <hr />
    <center>
        <a href="https://www.newcastle.edu.au/current-students/support/personal">Click Here For More Information</a>
    </center>
