<button class="servicesTab"> Transport: Getting On Campus </button>

<div class="panel">
    <hr />
    <p>
        Students can visit Callaghan campus through various modes of transportation. They can use bus, car,
        rideshare, shuttle service, etc. getting on campus is not a very big challenge nowadays.
        As Callaghan campus is approximately 12 kilometers from Newcastle CBD, you can go there by:
    </p>

    <h3>Active travel:</h3>
    <p>
        Walking and cycling are one of the ways through which you can reach the university. There are
        off roads paths to walk and cycling space on roads as well. You can adopt it in your daily life
        if you live near university because it can be very helpful for your health and it has its own benefits
        in your daily life.
    </p>

    <h3>Bus:</h3>
    <p>
        Local bus stops are there on campus where you can access travel services around the campus.
        You can get access to the bus from the design building to the mathematics building to university drive.
        You can access more information from: <a href="https://www.newcastle.edu.au/campus-life/newcastle/callaghan/getting-here">Getting Here</a>
    </p>

    <h3>Car:</h3>
    <p>
        There is a lot of parking on campus. You must pay for the parking if you don’t have a parking permit.
        If you want to get parking permit, follow these steps:
        <ul>
            <li>Login to the online shop</li>
            <li>Follow the steps and purchase the permit</li>
            <li>Print the order</li>
            <li>Take your permit and paste it on your front mirror.</li>
        </ul>
        <br />
        There is also free parking at P16 (parking 16).
        <a href="https://www.newcastle.edu.au/campus-life/newcastle/callaghan/map">Click here to search more parking information.</a>
    </p>

    <h3>Shuttle Service:</h3>
    <p>
        University also runs a shuttle bus service during semester days. It is known as security shuttle,
        and it runs during the semester from Monday to Friday. If you want to go home at night, this service
        is available for you, and it will drop you to your destination safely near university.
        <br /> <br />
        If students are coming from new space campus. They can have a bus service from king street that will
        take students to Callaghan campus. This service runs during the semester. During your exams and semester
        periods, the shuttle runs with a 30-minute interval from 7:00 am to 10:15 am.

    </p>
